  <md:title>Demography and Population</md:title>
  <md:abstract><para id="para-00001">By the end of this section, you should be able to:</para><list id="list-00001">
<item>Explain demographic measurements like fertility and mortality rates</item>
<item>Describe a variety of demographic theories, such as Malthusian, cornucopian, zero population growth, and demographic transition theories</item>
<item>Evaluate current population trends and patterns</item>
<item>Differentiate between an internally displaced person, an asylum-seeker, and a refugee</item>
</list></md:abstract>
  <md:uuid>aaec018d-a1e6-4e6d-9d85-36f8274a9085</md:uuid>
